HEADWORD: Punitory
<hw>Pu"ni*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Punishing; tending
to punishment; punitive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God . . . may make moral evil, as well as natural, at the same
time both prudential and <qex>punitory</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>A.
Tucker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

